#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thig2.3:3.1"
msgid "3. Sumaṅgalamātātherīgāthā"
msgstr "2.3. Sumaṅgala’s Mother"

# See Norman on readings.
#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc23"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts23"></a><a class="pts" id="pts126"></a>
msgctxt "thig2.3:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Sumuttikā <span class=\"var\" title=\"sumuttike sumuttike (bj) | sumuttike "
"sumuttikā (s2, s3, pts1-2, mr)\" id=\"note16\">sumuttikā</span>,"
msgstr "I’m well freed, well freed,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:4.2"
msgid "Sādhumuttikāmhi musalassa;"
msgstr "so very well freed!"

# See Norman for the textual problems here. Comm says gihikāle and it must be historical present. Adopting the commentary's vāto for the obscure chattakam, and vāti for vāpi, I propose that we keep musalassa as genitive and (normalizing the syntax a little), read as: musalassa me ahiriko vāto vāti; ukkhalikā me deḍḍubhaṃ vāti.
#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:4.3"
msgid "Ahiriko me chattakaṃ vāpi,"
msgstr "My pestle’s shameless wind was wafting;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:4.4"
msgid "Ukkhalikā me deḍḍubhaṃ vāti."
msgstr "my little pot wafted like an eel."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc24"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts24"></a>
msgctxt "thig2.3:5.1"
msgid "Rāgañca ahaṃ dosañca,"
msgstr "Now, as for greed and hate:"

# Cicciti recalls the sound of frying. The metaphorical progress should be captured in the rendering: formerly, her cookery—whether read literally or as metaphor—was shameful and unpleasant; but now she uses the same powers to destroy the defilements.
#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:5.2"
msgid "Cicciṭi cicciṭīti vihanāmi;"
msgstr "I sear them and sizzle them up."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:5.3"
msgid "Sā rukkhamūlamupagamma,"
msgstr "Having gone to the root of a tree,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thig2.3:5.4"
msgid "Aho sukhanti sukhato jhāyāmī”ti."
msgstr "I meditate happily, thinking, “Oh, what bliss!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
